Preconditions:
The input matrix `mat` is not null.
The input matrix `mat` has at least one row and one column.
The input matrix `mat` contains only non-negative integers.
The input integer `threshold` is non-negative.

Postconditions:
The method returns an integer value representing the maximum side-length of a square with a sum less than or equal to the threshold.
If there is no square with a sum less than or equal to the threshold, the method returns 0.